01/08/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- At least 13 people died of sunstroke or dehydration during the recent prolonged heat wave, authorities reported Saturday (30 July). 
In Bucharest, temperatures soared to 38 degrees Celsius. 
Emergency services reported that they responded to 1,300 calls in 30 hours. 
Earlier in July, flooding devastated parts of the country. 
(Reuters - 30/07/05)
